{
  "text": "Desirability function, just like risk analysis, is a quality tool first proposed by Harrington in 1965 for use in the optimization of quality of manufactured products. The approach has basic foundation in engineering [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and is widely adopted in the manufacturing industry.",
